<div id="v520.9.5"><span class="G3739 s">Whose</span><span class="G3962 s"> <i>are</i> the fathers</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G1537 s"> of</span><span class="G3739 s"> whom</span><span class="G2596 s"> as concerning</span><span class="G4561 s"> the flesh</span><span class="G5547 s"> Christ</span><span class="G5607 s"> <i>came</i>, who</span><span class="G1909 s"> is over</span><span class="G3956 s"> all</span><span class="G2316 s">, God</span><span class="G2128 s"> blessed</span><span class="G1519 s"> for</span><span class="G165 s"> ever</span><span class="G281 s">. Amen</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.9.6"><span class="G3756 s">Not</span><span class="G3634 s"> as</span><span class="G1161 s"> though</span><span class="G3056 s"> G3754 the word</span><span class="G2316 s"> of God</span><span class="G1601 s"> hath taken none effect</span><span class="G1063 s">. For</span><span class="G3756 s"> they <i>are</i> not</span><span class="G3956 s"> all</span><span class="G2474 s"> G1537 Israel</span><span class="G3588 s">, which</span><span class="G2474 s"> G3778 are of Israel</span>:</div>
<div id="v520.9.7"><span class="G3761 s">Neither</span><span class="G3754 s">, because</span><span class="G1526 s"> they are</span><span class="G4690 s"> the seed</span><span class="G11 s"> of Abraham</span><span class="G3956 s">, <i>are they</i> all</span><span class="G5043 s"> children</span><span class="G235 s">: but</span><span class="G1722 s">, In</span><span class="G2464 s"> Isaac</span><span class="G2564 s"> shall</span><span class="G4671 s"> thy</span><span class="G4690 s"> seed</span><span class="G2564 s"> be called</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.9.8"><span class="G5123 s">That is</span><span class="G5043 s">, They which are the children</span><span class="G4561 s"> of the flesh</span><span class="G5023 s">, these</span><span class="G3756 s"> <i>are</i> not</span><span class="G5043 s"> the children</span><span class="G2316 s"> of God</span><span class="G235 s">: but</span><span class="G5043 s"> the children</span><span class="G1860 s"> of the promise</span><span class="G3049 s"> are counted</span><span class="G1519 s"> for</span><span class="G4690 s"> the seed</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.9.9"><span class="G1063 s">For</span><span class="G3778 s"> this</span><span class="G3056 s"> <i>is</i> the word</span><span class="G1860 s"> of promise</span><span class="G2596 s">, At</span><span class="G5126 s"> this</span><span class="G2540 s"> time</span><span class="G2064 s"> will I come</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G4564 s"> Sarah</span><span class="G2071 s"> shall have</span><span class="G5207 s"> a son</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.9.10"><span class="G1161 s">And</span><span class="G3756 s"> not</span><span class="G3440 s"> only</span><span class="G235 s"> <i>this</i>; but</span><span class="G4479 s"> when Rebecca</span><span class="G2532 s"> also</span><span class="G2845 s"> had conceived</span><span class="G1537 s"> by</span><span class="G1520 s"> one</span><span class="G2257 s"> G2192, <i>even</i> by our</span><span class="G3962 s"> father</span><span class="G2464 s"> Isaac</span>;</div>
<div id="v520.9.11"><span class="G1063 s">(For</span><span class="G1080 s"> <i>the children</i> being</span><span class="G3380 s"> not yet</span><span class="G1080 s"> born</span><span class="G3366 s">, neither</span><span class="G4238 s"> having done</span><span class="G5100 s"> any</span><span class="G18 s"> good</span><span class="G2228 s"> or</span><span class="G2556 s"> evil</span><span class="G2443 s">, that</span><span class="G4286 s"> the purpose</span><span class="G2316 s"> of God</span><span class="G2596 s"> according</span><span class="G1589 s"> to election</span><span class="G3306 s"> might stand</span><span class="G3756 s">, not</span><span class="G1537 s"> of</span><span class="G2041 s"> works</span><span class="G235 s">, but</span><span class="G1537 s"> of</span><span class="G2564 s"> him that calleth</span>;)</div>
<div id="v520.9.12"><span class="G3754 s">â€ </span><span class="G4483 s"> It was said</span><span class="G846 s"> unto her</span><span class="G3187 s">, The elder</span><span class="G1398 s"> shall serve</span><span class="G1640 s"> the younger</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (elder: or, greater) (elder: or, greater) (younger: or, lesser)</span></div>
<div id="v520.9.13"><span class="G2531 s">As</span><span class="G1125 s"> it is written</span><span class="G2384 s">, Jacob</span><span class="G25 s"> have I loved</span><span class="G1161 s">, but</span><span class="G2269 s"> Esau</span><span class="G3404 s"> have I hated</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.9.14"><span class="G5101 s">What</span><span class="G2046 s"> shall we say</span><span class="G3767 s"> then</span><span class="G93 s"> G3361? <i>Is there</i> unrighteousness</span><span class="G3844 s"> with</span><span class="G2316 s"> God</span><span class="G3361 s">? God forbid</span> G1096.</div>
<div id="v520.9.15"><span class="G1063 s">For</span><span class="G3004 s"> he saith</span><span class="G3475 s"> to Moses</span><span class="G1653 s">, I will have mercy on</span><span class="G3739 s"> whom</span><span class="G1653 s"> G302 I will have mercy</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G3627 s"> I will have compassion</span><span class="G3739 s"> on whom</span><span class="G3627 s"> G302 I will have compassion</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.9.16"><span class="G686 s">So</span><span class="G3767 s"> then</span><span class="G3756 s"> <i>it is</i> not</span><span class="G2309 s"> of him that willeth</span><span class="G3761 s">, nor</span><span class="G5143 s"> of him that runneth</span><span class="G235 s">, but</span><span class="G2316 s"> of God</span><span class="G1653 s"> that sheweth mercy</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.9.17"><span class="G1063 s">For</span><span class="G1124 s"> the scripture</span><span class="G3004 s"> saith</span><span class="G5328 s"> unto Pharaoh</span><span class="G3754 s">, Even for</span><span class="G5124 s"> G1519 this</span><span class="G846 s"> same purpose</span><span class="G1825 s"> have I raised</span><span class="G4571 s"> thee</span><span class="G1825 s"> up</span><span class="G3704 s">, that</span><span class="G1731 s"> I might shew</span><span class="G3450 s"> my</span><span class="G1411 s"> power</span><span class="G1722 s"> in</span><span class="G4671 s"> thee</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G3704 s"> that</span><span class="G3450 s"> my</span><span class="G3686 s"> name</span><span class="G1229 s"> might be declared</span><span class="G1722 s"> throughout</span><span class="G3956 s"> all</span><span class="G1093 s"> the earth</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.9.18"><span class="G686 s">Therefore</span><span class="G1653 s"> G3767 hath he mercy</span><span class="G3739 s"> on whom</span><span class="G2309 s"> he will</span><span class="G1161 s"> <i>have mercy</i>, and</span><span class="G3739 s"> whom</span><span class="G2309 s"> he will</span><span class="G4645 s"> he hardeneth</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.9.19"><span class="G2046 s">Thou wilt say</span><span class="G3767 s"> then</span><span class="G3427 s"> unto me</span><span class="G5101 s">, Why</span><span class="G2089 s"> doth he yet</span><span class="G3201 s"> find fault</span><span class="G1063 s">? For</span><span class="G5101 s"> who</span><span class="G436 s"> hath resisted</span><span class="G846 s"> his</span><span class="G1013 s"> will</span>?</div>
<div id="v520.9.20"><span class="G3304 s">Nay but</span><span class="G5599 s">, O</span><span class="G444 s"> man</span><span class="G5101 s">, who</span><span class="G1488 s"> art</span><span class="G4771 s"> thou</span><span class="G470 s"> that repliest against</span><span class="G2316 s"> God</span><span class="G2046 s"> G3361? Shall</span><span class="G4110 s"> the thing formed</span><span class="G2046 s"> say</span><span class="G4111 s"> to him that formed</span><span class="G5101 s"> <i>it</i>, Why</span><span class="G4160 s"> hast thou made</span><span class="G3165 s"> me</span><span class="G3779 s"> thus</span>? <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (repliestâ€¦: or, answerest again, or, disputest with God?)</span></div>
<div id="v520.9.21"><span class="G2228 s">â€ </span><span class="G2192 s"> Hath</span><span class="G3756 s"> not</span><span class="G2763 s"> the potter</span><span class="G1849 s"> power</span><span class="G4081 s"> over the clay</span><span class="G1537 s">, of</span><span class="G846 s"> the same</span><span class="G5445 s"> lump</span><span class="G3739 s"> to</span><span class="G4160 s"> G3303 make</span><span class="G4632 s"> one vessel</span><span class="G1519 s"> unto</span><span class="G5092 s"> honour</span><span class="G1161 s">, and</span><span class="G3739 s"> another</span><span class="G1519 s"> unto</span><span class="G819 s"> dishonour</span>?</div>
<div id="v520.9.22"><span class="G1487 s"><i>What</i> if</span><span class="G2316 s"> G1161 God</span><span class="G2309 s">, willing</span><span class="G1731 s"> to shew</span><span class="G3709 s"> <i>his</i> wrath</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G1107 s"> to make</span><span class="G846 s"> his</span><span class="G1415 s"> power</span><span class="G1107 s"> known</span><span class="G5342 s">, endured</span><span class="G1722 s"> with</span><span class="G4183 s"> much</span><span class="G3115 s"> longsuffering</span><span class="G4632 s"> the vessels</span><span class="G3709 s"> of wrath</span><span class="G2675 s"> fitted</span><span class="G1519 s"> to</span><span class="G684 s"> destruction</span>: <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (fitted: or, made up)</span></div>
<div id="v520.9.23"><span class="G2532 s">And</span><span class="G2443 s"> that</span><span class="G1107 s"> he might make known</span><span class="G4149 s"> the riches</span><span class="G846 s"> of his</span><span class="G1391 s"> glory</span><span class="G1909 s"> on</span><span class="G4632 s"> the vessels</span><span class="G1656 s"> of mercy</span><span class="G3739 s">, which</span><span class="G4282 s"> he had afore prepared</span><span class="G1519 s"> unto</span><span class="G1391 s"> glory</span>,</div>
<div id="v520.9.24"><span class="G3739 s">â€ </span><span class="G2532 s"> Even</span><span class="G2248 s"> us</span><span class="G3739 s">, whom</span><span class="G2564 s"> he hath called</span><span class="G3756 s">, not</span><span class="G1537 s"> of</span><span class="G2453 s"> the Jews</span><span class="G3440 s"> only</span><span class="G235 s">, but</span><span class="G2532 s"> also</span><span class="G1537 s"> of</span><span class="G1484 s"> the Gentiles</span>?</div>
<div id="v520.9.25"><span class="G3004 s">As he saith</span><span class="G2532 s"> also</span><span class="G1722 s"> in</span><span class="G5617 s"> Osee</span><span class="G2564 s">, I will call</span><span class="G3450 s"> them my</span><span class="G2992 s"> people</span><span class="G3756 s">, which were not</span><span class="G3450 s"> my</span><span class="G2992 s"> people</span><span class="G2532 s">; and</span><span class="G25 s"> her beloved</span><span class="G25 s">, which was</span><span class="G3756 s"> not</span><span class="G25 s"> beloved</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.9.26"><span class="G2532 s">And</span><span class="G2071 s"> it shall come to pass</span><span class="G1722 s">, <i>that</i> in</span><span class="G5117 s"> the place</span><span class="G3757 s"> where</span><span class="G4483 s"> G3739 it was said</span><span class="G846 s"> unto them</span><span class="G5210 s">, Ye</span><span class="G3756 s"> <i>are</i> not</span><span class="G3450 s"> my</span><span class="G2992 s"> people</span><span class="G1563 s">; there</span><span class="G2564 s"> shall they be called</span><span class="G5207 s"> the children</span><span class="G2198 s"> of the living</span><span class="G2316 s"> God</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.9.27"><span class="G2268 s">Esaias</span><span class="G1161 s"> also</span><span class="G2896 s"> crieth</span><span class="G5228 s"> concerning</span><span class="G2474 s"> Israel</span><span class="G1437 s">, Though</span><span class="G706 s"> the number</span><span class="G5207 s"> of the children</span><span class="G2474 s"> of Israel</span><span class="G5600 s"> be</span><span class="G5613 s"> as</span><span class="G285 s"> the sand</span><span class="G2281 s"> of the sea</span><span class="G2640 s">, a remnant</span><span class="G4982 s"> shall be saved</span>:</div>
<div id="v520.9.28"><span class="G1063 s">For</span><span class="G4931 s"> he will finish</span><span class="G3056 s"> the work</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G4932 s"> cut <i>it</i> short</span><span class="G1722 s"> in</span><span class="G1343 s"> righteousness</span><span class="G3754 s">: because</span><span class="G4932 s"> a short</span><span class="G3056 s"> work</span><span class="G4160 s"> will</span><span class="G2962 s"> the Lord</span><span class="G4160 s"> make</span><span class="G1909 s"> upon</span><span class="G1093 s"> the earth</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (the work: or, the account)</span></div>
<div id="v520.9.29"><span class="G2532 s">And</span><span class="G2531 s"> as</span><span class="G2268 s"> Esaias</span><span class="G4280 s"> said before</span><span class="G1508 s">, Except</span><span class="G2962 s"> the Lord</span><span class="G4519 s"> of Sabaoth</span><span class="G1459 s"> had left</span><span class="G2254 s"> us</span><span class="G4690 s"> a seed</span><span class="G302 s">, we had been</span><span class="G5613 s"> G1096 as</span><span class="G4670 s"> Sodoma</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G302 s"> been made like</span><span class="G5613 s"> G3666 unto</span><span class="G1116 s"> Gomorrha</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.9.30"><span class="G5101 s">What</span><span class="G2046 s"> shall we say</span><span class="G3767 s"> then</span><span class="G3754 s">? That</span><span class="G1484 s"> the Gentiles</span><span class="G3588 s">, which</span><span class="G1377 s"> followed</span><span class="G3361 s"> not</span><span class="G1343 s"> after righteousness</span><span class="G2638 s">, have attained</span><span class="G1343 s"> to righteousness</span><span class="G1161 s">, even</span><span class="G1343 s"> the righteousness</span><span class="G3588 s"> which</span><span class="G1537 s"> is of</span><span class="G4102 s"> faith</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.9.31"><span class="G1161 s">But</span><span class="G2474 s"> Israel</span><span class="G1377 s">, which followed</span><span class="G3551 s"> after the law</span><span class="G1343 s"> of righteousness</span><span class="G5348 s">, hath</span><span class="G3756 s"> not</span><span class="G5348 s"> attained</span><span class="G1519 s"> to</span><span class="G3551 s"> the law</span><span class="G1343 s"> of righteousness</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.9.32"><span class="G1302 s">Wherefore</span><span class="G3754 s">? Because</span><span class="G3756 s"> <i>they sought it</i> not</span><span class="G1537 s"> by</span><span class="G4102 s"> faith</span><span class="G235 s">, but</span><span class="G5613 s"> as</span><span class="G1537 s"> it were by</span><span class="G2041 s"> the works</span><span class="G3551 s"> of the law</span><span class="G1063 s">. For</span><span class="G4350 s"> they stumbled</span><span class="G3037 s"> at that stumblingstone</span> G4348;</div>
<div id="v520.9.33"><span class="G2531 s">As</span><span class="G1125 s"> it is written</span><span class="G2400 s">, Behold</span><span class="G5087 s">, I lay</span><span class="G1722 s"> in</span><span class="G4622 s"> Sion</span><span class="G3037 s"> a stumblingstone</span><span class="G2532 s"> G4348 and</span><span class="G4073 s"> rock</span><span class="G4625 s"> of offence</span><span class="G2532 s">: and</span><span class="G3956 s"> whosoever</span><span class="G4100 s"> believeth</span><span class="G1909 s"> on</span><span class="G846 s"> him</span><span class="G2617 s"> shall</span><span class="G3756 s"> not</span><span class="G2617 s"> be ashamed</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (ashamed: or confounded)</span></div></div>
